    "description": "Are you a skilled Full Stack Developer looking for your next big career move? Broadcom India Asia Pacific Associates in Chennai offers you the perfect platform to grow professionally and personally.\n\nAbout Broadcom India Asia Pacific Associates:\nBroadcom India Asia Pacific Associates is a leading organization in the On-site sector, committed to excellence, innovation, and employee growth. We offer a dynamic work environment where talent is recognized and rewarded.\n\nKey Responsibilities:\n• Participate in code reviews and contribute to technical discussions\n• Participate in on-call rotation for production support\n• Collaborate with cross-functional teams including product, design, and QA\n• Write clean, maintainable, and well-documented code\n• Design, develop and maintain scalable software applications\n• Integrate third-party APIs and services\n• Ensure code security and follow best practices for data protection\n\nRequired Skills & Qualifications:\n• B.Ed / M.Ed from a recognized institution\n• 3-6 years of relevant experience\n• Proficiency in Agile/Scrum\n• Proficiency in REST APIs\n• Proficiency in Java\n• Proficiency in SQL\n• Proficiency in React\n• Proficiency in Docker\n• Proficiency in Node.js\n• Proficiency in AWS\n\nWork Mode: On-site - Work from our office\n\nWhat We Offer:\n• Provident Fund and Gratuity as per company policy\n• Annual paid leaves and casual leaves\n• Learning & development budget\n• Referral bonus program\n• Professional development and training programs\n• Work-from-home flexibility\n• Salary Range: 7 LPA - 15 LPA per annum\n\nLocation: Chennai, Tamil Nadu, India\n\nIf you are excited about this opportunity, apply now and take the next step in your career journey with Broadcom India Asia Pacific Associates!",
